# <gitmoji> <type>(<scope>): <English subject>
#
# [optional body]
#
# [optional footer(s)]
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# GITMOJI + CONVENTIONAL COMMITS REFERENCE (CutVi style)
# https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/
# https://gitmoji.dev
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# FORMAT
#   ✨ feat(login): add user login
#   🐛 fix(i18n): correct japanese placeholder key
#   📚 docs(readme): update setup instructions
#
# TYPE + GITMOJI
#   ✨  feat      New feature
#   🐛  fix       Bug fix
#   ♻️  refactor  Code restructure (no behavior change)
#   🎨  style     Formatting, whitespace, UI styling (no logic change)
#   📚  docs      Documentation only
#   ✅  test      Add or update tests
#   🔧  chore     Config, tooling, maintenance
#   🚀  perf      Performance improvement
#   📦  build     Build system, compiler settings, packages
#   👷  ci        CI/CD pipeline changes
#   🔥  remove    Remove files or features
#   🚑  hotfix    Critical production bug fix
#   🔖  release   Release tagging or version update
#   🔄  sync      Sync changes from boilerplate or upstream
#   🔒️  security  Security fix or hardening
#   ⏪️  revert    Revert a previous commit
#   💥  BREAKING  Breaking change (also add ! after type, e.g. feat!:)
#
# SCOPE (Required, must be lowercase kebab-case)
#   e.g. backend, frontend, auth, sync-script, code-style
#
# RULES (Conventional Commits)
#   - Scope: MUST be provided, lowercase kebab-case only.
#   - Subject line: MUST be written in English. Imperative mood, no period, ≤72 chars.
#   - Body: explain WHY, not WHAT (wrap at 72 chars)
#   - BREAKING CHANGE: add footer "BREAKING CHANGE: <description>"
#     or append ! to type: "feat!(scope): ..."
#   - Multiple footers allowed: "Closes #123", "Refs #456"
#
# EXAMPLES
#   ✨ feat(frontend): add png export button
#   🐛 fix(backend): handle missing drive folder on first run
#   🎨 style(button): adjust main primary hover color
#   🔒️ security(auth): enforce domain access in cookies
#   💥 feat!(backend): change savediagram return shape
#
#   BREAKING CHANGE: saveDiagram now returns { id, name } instead of id string
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
